#include <stdio.h> #include <stdlib.h> #define MAX_SIZE 10 // Stack int stack[MAX_SIZE]; int top = -1; void push(int data) {  if (top == MAX_SIZE - 1) {  printf("Stack overflow\n");  return;  }  stack[++top] = data; } int pop() {  if (top == -1) {  printf("Stack is empty\n");  return -1;  }  return stack[top--]; } int isStackEmpty() {  return top == -1; } // Queue int queue[MAX_SIZE]; int front = -1, rear = -1; void enqueue(int data) {  if (rear == MAX_SIZE - 1) {  printf("Queue is full\n");  return;  }  queue[++rear] = data; } int dequeue() {  if (front == rear) {  printf("Queue is empty\n");  return -1;  }  return queue[++front]; } int isQueueEmpty() {  return front == rear; } // Circular Queue int cqueue[MAX_SIZE]; void cenqueue(int data) {  if ((rear + 1) % MAX_SIZE == front) {  printf("Circular Queue is full\n");  return;  }  rear = (rear + 1) % MAX_SIZE;  cqueue[rear] = data; } int cdequeue() {  if (front == rear) {  printf("Circular Queue is empty\n");  return -1;  }  front = (front + 1) % MAX_SIZE;  return cqueue[front]; } int isCircularQueueEmpty() {  return front == rear; } int main() {  // Stack Operations  printf("Stack Implementation:\n");  push(1);  push(2);  printf("Popped from Stack: %d\n", pop());  printf("Popped from Stack: %d\n", pop());  // Queue Operations  printf("\nQueue Implementation:\n");  enqueue(3);  enqueue(4);  printf("Dequeued from Queue: %d\n", dequeue());  printf("Dequeued from Queue: %d\n", dequeue());  // Circular Queue Operations  printf("\nCircular Queue Implementation:\n");  cenqueue(5);  cenqueue(6);  printf("Dequeued from Circular Queue: %d\n", cdequeue());  printf("Dequeued from Circular Queue: %d\n", cdequeue());  return 0; }

My theory of LCU: At 1:55, the chair in which Anthony Das (Sanjay Dutt) is sitting is the same as Rolex (Suriya) from Vikram movie. The body language of Herald Das (Arjun) is very similar to that of Rolex. Rolex might have been working with Das and co in his past.  Since Rolex says he didn't inherit this drug empire from his dad or his grandfather, he might have somehow defeated or made Das and co his enemy and became a kingpin now. We may see his character mentioned in Leo.  The story of Leo is rumoured to be that of "A history of violence". So Leo Das (Vijay) for some reason, left his family business and came to lead a normal Life. He is no longer a part of the drug empire. So he might not be shown in the future part of LCU development. Or I might be wrong if Lokesh has a plan of extending Leo's character through a lead in the climax.  If anyone have contrary perspective please share and let us discuss. Thank you for reading this till the end.

Where can I stream the Tamil Song Badass from the movie Leo? Badasss ma ğŸ”¥ğŸ”¥
I believe the greatest form of love is shone to us by sacrifice. What we are willing to give up for the love of someone else. Too often and too frequently is life filled with bitterness, anger, hatred, and jealousy. Just imagine what kind of world it would be if we all loved one another, if we all cared, and had concern for each other. That we all did our best to make sure life was good for everyone.  That no one was homeless, that no one faced despair, rejection, or pains of loneliness and self-doubt. That there were no more wars, wars built on greed, and man's fear of each other, fear of the unknown. I think of the ultimate sacrifice when a carpenter named Jesus Christ from Bethlehem faced beatings, whippings, insults, injury, and crucifixion for our sins. who died so we could become righteous, to never again face the fear of death or the nightmares of hell ever again. a righteousness we could never earn unto ourselves, not based on our performance, but given to us as a gift of mercy. None of us are righteous, perfect or good (any human who claims that is untruthful with you)  we have all sinned before God. Everyday we make mistakes and everyday we sin in word, thought, action and deed, but God loved us so much that he look past our frail human nature and our failures and loved us and wanted to save us anyway despite the fact we could never be good or righteous on our own merit.  Knowing that a man is not justified by the works of the law, but by the faith of Jesus Christ, even we have believed in Jesus Christ,  that we might be justified by the faith of Christ,  and not by the works of the law: for by the works of the law shall no flesh be justified. Galatians 2:16 Therefore no one will be declared righteous in Godâ€™s sight by the works of the law; rather, through the law we become conscious of our sin. Romans 3:20 For whoever keeps the whole law and yet stumbles at just one point is guilty of breaking all of it. James 2:10  But Samuel replied: â€œDoes the LORD delight in burnt offerings and sacrifices as much as in obeying the LORD? That's why while we live we need to turn to God for forgiveness. LyricistÂ Vishnu EdavanÂ has penned Badass song lyrics from Leo and the movie is directed byÂ Lokesh Kanagaraj. It starsÂ Thalapathy Vijay, Trisha KrishnanÂ in the lead roles. The music of this amazing song is composed byÂ Anirudh Ravichander. Here we present to you the exclusive lyrics of the Tamil song Badass from the movie Leo.   Badass song featured in the latest Thalapathy Vijay feature film Leo is composed by rockstar Anirudh Ravichander. The song is more like an introduction of the lead character ofÂ Leo DasÂ portrayed by Thalapathy Vijay in the movie. Lyrics penned by Vishnu Edavan feature words that refer to valiance and courage and easily emerges as a winner in showcasing the mass transformation of Leo Das. Anirudh's rocking music with exhilarating beats give profound importance to energy than melody and easily captivates the attention of the fans of Ilaya Thalapathy. Badass song from Leo can easily get into your playlists and especially among your picks for morning motivation and workout songs.
